OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,FThe body of one of the victims of the
OL,7,FNottingham attacks was kept at the
OL,8,Fcrime scene for nearly 15 hours while
OL,9,Fpolice were investigating, the inquiry
OL,10,Finto the attacks has heard.
OL,12,F65-year-old Ian Coates was fatally
OL,13,Fstabbed by Valdo Calocane over an hour
OL,14,Fafter undergraduates Barnaby Webber
OL,15,Fand Grace O'Malley Kumar, both 19,
OL,16,Fwere killed in June 2023.
OL,18,FAfter stealing Mr Coate's van,
OL,19,FCalocane ran over and seriously
OL,20,Finjured three pedestrians.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,FThe official inquiry into the attacks,
OL,7,Fwhere three people were killed in June
OL,8,F2023, is underway in central London
OL,9,Fand started a month ago.
OL,11,FJulian Blake, counsel to the inquiry,
OL,12,Fasked the temporary Deputy Chief
OL,13,FConstable Rob Griffin from
OL,14,FNottinghamshire Police, if it was
OL,15,Funusual that Mr Coates - who was
OL,16,Fpronounced dead at 5.52am - was kept
OL,17,Fat the scene until 8.30pm.
OL,19,FMr Griffin said he was made aware of
OL,20,Fthis only recently, adding: "It does
OL,21,Fseem like a long time.
OL,26,@|D@]OU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,F"For Ian's family, that's particularly
OL,7,Ftraumatic.
OL,9,F"But given the number of scenes being
OL,10,Fmanaged at the time, the availability
OL,11,Fof crime scene investigators, the
OL,12,Fapproach taken by the crime scene co-
OL,13,Fordinator, and the thoroughness with
OL,14,Fwhich that scene was being managed, I
OL,15,Fhave to trust those who say that
OL,16,Famount of time was necessary in order
OL,17,Fto ensure all forensic opportunity was
OL,18,Fmaximised.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,F"Unfortunately, I can't go any further
OL,7,Fthan that because I haven't personally
OL,8,Finvestigated every single document
OL,9,Fthat relates to that matter."
OL,11,FThe inquiry heard that police waited
OL,12,Fmonths before telling bereaved
OL,13,Ffamilies that staff had
OL,14,Finappropriately viewed images and
OL,15,Ffootage of the attacks.
OL,17,FIn September 2023, Mr Griffin became
OL,18,Faware that a special constable had
OL,19,Fviewed images related to the attacks
OL,20,Fwith no policing purpose, the inquiry
OL,21,Fwas told.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@]O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,FMr Griffin said it was the senior
OL,7,Finvestigating officer's responsibility
OL,8,Fto inform families of misconduct.
OL,10,FHowever, he added: "I regret that
OL,11,Fbetween September 20 and December 14
OL,12,F(2023), I missed an opportunity in
OL,13,Fthat period to step into that space
OL,14,Fand be more intrusive to ensure that
OL,15,Finformation was shared. I thought it
OL,16,Fhad been.
OL,26,@rD@TOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1774372288
OL,3,CBody of Nottingham attacks victim kept
OL,4,Cat crime scene for 15 hours
OL,6,F"All of that pain, additional pain,
OL,7,Fthat the bereaved families and
OL,8,Fsurviving victims have suffered
OL,9,Fbecause of that could have been
OL,10,Favoided if I'd have stepped into that
OL,11,Fspace and made sure that it happened.
OL,13,F"I'm really sorry about that."
OL,15,FThe inquiry continues.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUuD@^O]
